title.narrative: CHILD PROTECTION SOUTH SYRIA

description.narrative: South Syria: Syria's conflict-affected population have their critical Child Protection needs met, in line with the HRP and as part of the UNICEF JOP., which contributes to Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: MENARO delivers timely, equitable and principled humanitarian action as a complement to country office-led operations where required, including through the cross-border component of the Syria programmes as part of the Whole of Syria response.

description.narrative: UNICEF's cross-border child protection (CP) programme focused on reaching children in areas formerly held by ISIL and deepening child protection work, including through Whole of Syria (WOS) CP Area of responsibility (AOR) coordination. Programming reached 81,829 children as of December2019 including through psychosocial support (PSS), awareness raising and case management services. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:09/04/2020
